This paper is about Tabled Constraint Logic Programming (CLP), which is a subfield of Programming Languages (PL) and Artificial Intelligence (AI). The paper also mentions applications in program analysis and model checking, which are related to Software Engineering (SE) and Logic (LO). Finally, the paper proposes a novel technique for compacting answer sets, which is related to Data Structures (DS). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.PL and cs.AI, followed by cs.LO, cs.SE, and cs.DS.
